  "name": "Breath of the Dragon",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "icons/creatures/abilities/dragon-ice-breath-blue.webp",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>At 3rd level you can channel destructive waves of energy, like those created by the dragons you emulate. When you take the <strong>Attack </strong>action on your turn, you can replace one of the attacks with an exhalation of draconic energy in either a 20-foot cone or a 30-foot line that is 5 feet wide (your choice). Choose a damage type: <strong>acid</strong>, <strong>cold</strong>, <strong>fire</strong>, <strong>lightning</strong>, or <strong>poison</strong>. Each creature in that area must make a <strong>Dexterity saving throw</strong> against your ki save DC, taking damage of the chosen type equal to two rolls of your @Compendium[5e-complete.5e-class-features.TMeKDQLocSb3loVv]{Martial Arts} die on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p>\n<p>At 11th level, the damage of this feature increases to three rolls of your Martial Arts die.</p>\n<p>You can use this feature a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus, and you regain all expended uses when you finish a <strong>long rest</strong>. While you have no uses available, you can spend 2 @Compendium[5e-complete.5e-class-features.imsZ2GYUPlwCQqqy]{ki points} to use this feature again.</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p><em>Note: Remember to change this feature's area of effect as desired before rolling.</em></p>\n<p><em>This feature is configured with limited uses; manually deduct your ki points if you spend them on this feature.</em></p>\n</section>",
